    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-07-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-07-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="956"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d956">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.00/1669.</note>
                <head>[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-07-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 20, 1911</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A revolution is set for July 26. The Zelayista junta in Salvador has sent an
                    agent to procure the help of President Cabrera of Guatemala, who has been trying
                    to defeat the Nicaragua loan project, and is cooperating with Saldivar,
                    ex-President of Salvador, for the overthrow of Diaz. The Zelayista leader, José
                    D. Gámez, has been conspiring with Saldivar’s daughter, Tona. The foregoing
                    advices come from the Nicaraguan chargé d’affaires in Salvador to the
                    President.</p>
                <p>The Nicaraguan Government knows there are deposits of arms but can not locate
                    them.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gunther.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
